swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information.

swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.name: swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort
swDevInfoTotalNumOfPort.description: The number of ports within this switch. This value is the sum of the ports within this switch.

swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.name: swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse
swDevInfoNumOfPortInUse.description: The number of ports in this switch connected to the segment or the end stations.

swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. The first four octets are defined as system LED. The first two octets are currently unused and must be set to zero. The third octet indicates the power LED. The fourth octet indicates the console LED. The fifth LED is RPS (Redundancy Power Supply) LED. The sixth LED is SD card LED, the following description is for SD card LED: 01 = SD card is not present. 02 = SD card is present. 03 = fails to read/write SD card. 04 = read/write SD card successfully. The other octets are the logical port LED. Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presented as the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented as the Speed LED. System LED: 01 = fail/error/non existence. 02 = work normal Link/Activity LED : The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second most significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. The four remaining bits are currently unused and must be 0.

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can enable or disable the spanning tree algorithm during the runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates if the layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can enable or disable RMON.

swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState.name: swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState
swL2DevCtrlSnmpTrapState.description: This object controls the SNMP trap status.

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: When the object is set to active, all statistical counters will be cleared. If set to normal, no action.

swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.name: swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl
swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.description: Indicates the VLAN ID to which the Dot1dTpFdbTable belongs; The default value is DEFAULT_VLAN_ID of the system.

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enable or disable MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of MAC addresses in the MAC Address table. The default value is 1 .

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval, in seconds, which will trigger MAC notification messages.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.name: swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState
swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetState
swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.description: This object controls the Telnet status.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlTelnetTcpPort.description: This object designates TCP ports. When Telnet is disabled, this object is not accessible.

swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.name: swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId
swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.description: This object controls which previously created VLANs are included in the System IP Interface.

swL2DevCtrlWebState.name: swL2DevCtrlWebState
swL2DevCtrlWebState.description: This object controls the Web status.

swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.name: swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort
swL2DevCtrlWebTcpPort.description: This object designates TCP ports. When Web is disabled, this object is not accessible.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.description: Specifies the state of the LLDP function. When this function is enabled, the switch can start to transmit LLDP packets and receive and process the LLDP packets. The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For the receiving of LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward_message is enabled, the received LLDP Data Unit packets will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig.name: swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig
swL2DevCtrlIpAutoconfig.description: This object controls the IP auto configuration state.

swL2DevCtrlCFMState.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMState
swL2DevCtrlCFMState.description: This object indicates the CFM global state.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortTable.description: A table containing the CFM state of specified ports.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortEntry.description: The entry of the CFM state on specified ports.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState.name: swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState
swL2DevCtrlCFMPortState.description: This object indicates the CFM state by port.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decides whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the switch topology changes. If the object is enabled(3), the topologyChange trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port transition, the device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the link was changed. If the object is enabled(3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its ports link change. The device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or other.

swL2VlanStaticTable.name: swL2VlanStaticTable
swL2VlanStaticTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

swL2VlanStaticEntry.name: swL2VlanStaticEntry
swL2VlanStaticEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex
swL2VlanIndex.description: The VLAN-ID or other identifier referring to this VLAN.

swL2VLANAdvertisement.name: swL2VLANAdvertisement
swL2VLANAdvertisement.description: This object indicates if the advertisement is active or not.

swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.name: swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState
swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.description: This object controls the PVID auto assigment state. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is disabled, PVID only be changed by PVID configuration (user changes explicitly). The VLAN configuration will not automatically change PVID. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is enabled, PVID will be possibly changed by PVID or VLAN configuration. When user configures a port to VLAN X's untagged membership, this port's PVID will be updated with VLAN X. In the form of VLAN list command, PVID is updated with last item of VLAN list. When user removes a port from the untagged membership of the PVID's VLAN, the port's PVID will be assigned with 'default VLAN'.

swL2VlanPortInfoTable.name: swL2VlanPortInfoTable
swL2VlanPortInfoTable.description: A table containing vlan and port role information of each port.

swL2VlanPortInfoEntry.name: swL2VlanPortInfoEntry
swL2VlanPortInfoEntry.description: The table entry of vlan port information.

swL2VlanPortInfoVid.name: swL2VlanPortInfoVid
swL2VlanPortInfoVid.description: The VLAN-ID assigned to a special port

swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole.name: swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole
swL2VlanPortInfoPortRole.description: The port role of a special port.when none,it means this port is not belong to the vlan.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoMediumType.name: swL2PortInfoMediumType
swL2PortInfoMediumType.description: Indicates medium type of the port number.

swL2PortInfoUnitID.name: swL2PortInfoUnitID
swL2PortInfoUnitID.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the system

swL2PortInfoType.name: swL2PortInfoType
swL2PortInfoType.description: This object indicates the connector type of this port.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.name: swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled
swL2PortInfoErrorDisabled.description: This object indicates the blocking type of this port.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlMediumType.name: swL2PortCtrlMediumType
swL2PortCtrlMediumType.description: Indicates medium type of the port number.

swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex
swL2PortCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decides if the port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Chose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: The flow control mechanism is different between full duplex mode and half duplex mode. For half duplex mode, the jamming signal is asserted. For full duplex mode, IEEE 802.3x flow control function sends PAUSE frames and receives PAUSE frames.

swL2PortCtrlLearningState.name: swL2PortCtrlLearningState
swL2PortCtrlLearningState.description: This object decides if the port is locked or not.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object sets each port's MAC notification state.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrame.description: This object configures the switch's jumbo frame settings.

swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.name: swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize
swL2PortCtrlJumboFrameMaxSize.description: This object describes how many bytes the max jumbo frame is.

swL2PortCounterCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlTable
swL2PortCounterCtrlTable.description: A table that used to clear counter information about every port.

swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry
swL2PortCounterCtrlEntry.description: A list of entry used to clear counter information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCounterCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCounterClearCtrl.name: swL2PortCounterClearCtrl
swL2PortCounterClearCtrl.description: This object indicates if to clear the counters for each port of the device or not.

swL2PortErrTable.name: swL2PortErrTable
swL2PortErrTable.description: A table that contains error information for each port.

swL2PortErrEntry.name: swL2PortErrEntry
swL2PortErrEntry.description: A list of information regarding port errors on the device.

swL2PortErrPortIndex.name: swL2PortErrPortIndex
swL2PortErrPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module).

swL2PortErrPortState.name: swL2PortErrPortState
swL2PortErrPortState.description: This object indicates the port state is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.name: swL2PortErrPortConnStatus
swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.description: This object indicates whether the PortStatus is err-disabled or not.

swL2PortErrPortReason.name: swL2PortErrPortReason
swL2PortErrPortReason.description: This object describes if the reason for the port error is STP LBD or Storm control.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable
swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable.description: A table that contains information about multicast filter address.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry
swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry.description: A list of multicast filter address information for each profile ID.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileName.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileName
swL2MulticastFilterProfileName.description: Specifies a profile name for each multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterStatus.name: swL2MulticastFilterStatus
swL2MulticastFilterStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable
swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable.description: A table that contains information about multicast filter address.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry
swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry.description: A list of multicast filter address information for each profile ID.

swL2MulticastFilterFromIp.name: swL2MulticastFilterFromIp
swL2MulticastFilterFromIp.description: Specifies the head IP address of a multicast address range which will be binded to a multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterToIp.name: swL2MulticastFilterToIp
swL2MulticastFilterToIp.description: Specifies the tail IP address of a multicast address range which will be binded to a multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterAddressState.name: swL2MulticastFilterAddressState
swL2MulticastFilterAddressState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. Setting value to createAndGo(4) will add the multicast address list specified in swL2MulticastFilterFromIp and swL2MulticastFilterToIp to multicast filter profile. Setting value to destroy(6) will remove the multicast address list specified in swL2MulticastFilterFromIp and swL2MulticastFilterToIp from multicast filter profile.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable.description: A table that used to bind port to profile id.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry.description: A list of information that used to bind port to profile id.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess.description: This object indicates the access status for each port.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID.description: This object specifies a profile ID list for each port.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileSta.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileStatus
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileSta.description: Controls the multicast filter profile list which bind to each port. When set add(2), multicast filter profile ID list which specifies in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID will be bound to the port. When set delete(3), multicast filter profile ID list which specifies in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID will be unbound from the port. The attribute value reverts to 'other' once the action has been done.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.description: A table that contains information about max group number based on port.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.description: A list of max group number information for each port.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex.description: Specifies port number as table index.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup.description: Specifies maximum multicast filter group numbers for each port. Default value is 256.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates RX Rate(64Kbit/sec) of the specified port. Value 1024001 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates TX Rate(64Kbit/sec) of the specified port. Value 1024001 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The RxRate value comes from RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrites the locally configured RxRate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The TxRate value comes from RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrites the locally configured TxRate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.description: Indicates the maximum number of packets the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit before allowing the next lowest priority queue to transmit its packets. a value between 0 and 15 can be specified.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.description: Indicates the mechanism of QoS scheduling.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has seven hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 6 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value to assign to untagged packets received by the switch ports on the switch..

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: The value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.description: This object controls QoS scheduling Mechanism.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: A port security feature which controls the address leaning capability and traffic forwarding decisions. Each port can be enabled or disabled for this function. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned on this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as static entries. When the learned addresses number reaches N, any incoming packet without learned source addresses are discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates the secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses to be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout(3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after the aging timer expires. In this mode, when the locked address is aged out, the number of addresses that can be learned has to be increased by one. In deleteOnReset(4) mode - Locked addresses never age out unless the system restarts which will prevent port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates administration state of locking address.

swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl.name: swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl
swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl.description: Used to clear port security entries by port. Setting this value to 'start' will execute the clear action, Once cleared, the value returns to 'other'.

swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.name: swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState
swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.description: When enabled(2),whenever there's a new MAC address that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, traps will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged into the system.

swL2DhcpRelayState.name: swL2DhcpRelayState
swL2DhcpRelayState.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.name: swL2DhcpRelayHopCount
swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that DHCP packets can cross.

swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.name: swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold
swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the DHCP packet.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82State
swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay agent information option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.description: This object indicates if the checking mechanism of DHCP relay agent information option 82 is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.description: This object indicates the reforwarding policy of DHCP relay agent information option 82. replace(1) - replace the exiting option 82 field in messages. drop(2) - discard messages with existing option 82 field. keep(3) - retain the existing option 82 field messages.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.description: This table specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.description: A list of information that specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry resides in the table.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current active number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information that specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index number of the logical port trunk group. The trunk group number depends on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunk, you cannot configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicates the number of ports included in this Trunk group. The trunk port number depends on the existence of the module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunk group.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of trunk group. static : is static trunk group lacp : is LACP trunk group .

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkActivePort.name: swL2TrunkActivePort
swL2TrunkActivePort.description: The object indicates the active port of a special trunk group.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures to part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates which switch port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to the bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: This represents the port where ingress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: This represents the port where egress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled(2) - After writing this value to the object, the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. enabled(3) - This entry resides in the table.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of VLANs in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: Maximum number of multicast IP groups per VLAN in the layer 2 IGMP information table(swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the VLAN's IGMP function. Its scale depends on the current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If the VLAN is disabled, there is only one entry in the table, with an index of 1. If the VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the maximum number of entries can be 12, with an index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN ID. If the VLAN is disabled, the VID is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If the VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the VID is arranged from 1 to 12, in a fixed form. If the VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the VID setting can be changed from 1 to 4094 by the management user, and the VID in each entry must be unique within the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packets when none were sent by the host on the LAN. The timer works on a per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query messages if the timer expires. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a querier receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decides if the IGMP query is enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP function is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP function is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.name: swL2IGMPFastLeaveState
swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.description: This object indicates the fast_leave status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP fast-leave function is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP fast-leave function is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryVersion.name: swL2IGMPQueryVersion
swL2IGMPQueryVersion.description: Configure the IGMP version of query packet which will be sent by router.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the number current IGMP query packets which are captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of the associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the VID of associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function was enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, in per-VLAN basis. In case of IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.description: The information of the router port table.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.description: This object indicates the static portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.description: This object indicates the dynamic portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.description: This object indicates the forbidden portlist of the router port entry.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable
swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.description: The table contains the current IGMP snooping group information captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry
swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.description: Information about the current IGMP snooping group information which has been captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid
swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the individual IGMP snooping group table entry.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.description: This object identifies the group IP address which has been captured from the IGMP packet, on a per-VLAN basis.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.description: This object identifies the source addresses.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under INCLUDE mode.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under EXCLUDE mode.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount
swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount.description: This object indicates how many report packets were received by our device corresponding with this entry that has the IGMP function enabled, on a per-group basis.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime
swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime.description: This object indicates how long since the group was detected.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime
swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime.description: This object indicates the time left before this group will be aged out.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts
swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts.description: This object indicates the port number of the router ports.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry
swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry.description: This object specifies the maximum number of entries which can be learned by dynamic IP multicast

swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlTable
swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP dynamic IP multicast.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPDynIPMultCtrlEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP dynamic IP multicast.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState
swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState.description: This object is used to disable or enable the dynamic IP multicast feature in this VLAN.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge
swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge.description: This object is used to enable or disable aging on the dynamic IP multicast entry in this VLAN.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable
swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP Access Authentication configurations of the device.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry
swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP Access Authentication. The configuration is done per port.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort
swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.description: The index of the swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable. This object corresponds to the port being configured.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthState
swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.description: This object denotes the status of IGMP Access Authentication of the port.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifies that the port can just forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information which specifies the port with its traffic forwarding list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list to which the specific port can forward traffic.

swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanTable
swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanTable.description: A table that contains information about VLAN multicast filter mode.

swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanEntry
swL2MulticastFilterModeVlanEntry.description: A list of multicast filter mode information for each VLAN.

swL2MulticastFilterVlanMode.name: swL2MulticastFilterVlanMode
swL2MulticastFilterVlanMode.description: Specifies multicast filter mode for each VLAN.

swL2LoopDetectAdminState.name: swL2LoopDetectAdminState
swL2LoopDetectAdminState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection status for the system.

swL2LoopDetectInterval.name: swL2LoopDetectInterval
swL2LoopDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the interval value, the range is from 1 to 32767 seconds.

swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.name: swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime
swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.description: This object indicates the recover time, the range is from 60 to 1000000. The value of 0 disables the recover function.

swL2LoopDetectMode.name: swL2LoopDetectMode
swL2LoopDetectMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.name: swL2LoopDetectTrapMode
swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection trap mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectPortTable.name: swL2LoopDetectPortTable
swL2LoopDetectPortTable.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.

swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.name: swL2LoopDetectPortEntry
swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.

swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.name: swL2LoopDetectPortIndex
swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number. The range is from 1 to the maximum port number specified in the module

swL2LoopDetectPortState.name: swL2LoopDetectPortState
swL2LoopDetectPortState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection function state on the port.

swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN.name: swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN
swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN.description: This object indicates the VLAN list that has detected a loopback.

swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.name: swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus
swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.description: This object indicates the port status.

swL2macNotification.name: swL2macNotification
swL2macNotification.description: This trap indicates the MAC addresses variation in address table .

swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap.name: swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap
swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap.description: When the port_security trap is enabled, new MAC addresses that violate the pre-defined port security configuration will trigger trap messages to be sent out.

swL2PortLoopOccurred.name: swL2PortLoopOccurred
swL2PortLoopOccurred.description: The trap is sent when a Port loop occurs.

swL2PortLoopRestart.name: swL2PortLoopRestart
swL2PortLoopRestart.description: The trap is sent when a Port loop restarts after the interval time.

swL2VlanLoopOccurred.name: swL2VlanLoopOccurred
swL2VlanLoopOccurred.description: The trap is sent when a Port with a VID loop occurs.

swL2VlanLoopRestart.name: swL2VlanLoopRestart
swL2VlanLoopRestart.description: The trap is sent when a Port with a VID loop restarts after the interval time.

swL2macNotifyInfo.name: swL2macNotifyInfo
swL2macNotifyInfo.description: This object indicates the last time reboot information.

swL2PortSecurityViolationMac.name: swL2PortSecurityViolationMac
swL2PortSecurityViolationMac.description: This object indicates the MAC address that violates the port security configuration.

swL2VlanLoopDetectVID.name: swL2VlanLoopDetectVID
swL2VlanLoopDetectVID.description: This object indicates the VID that detected a loopback.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP local relay function of the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the DHCP local relay status for each VLAN.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.description: This object lists the current VLANs in the switch and their corresponding DHCP local relay status.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.description: This object shows the VIDs of the current VLANS in the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP relay function of the VLAN.
